came the subject of popular ballads and plays, which may well have increased the currency of the name in the 16th century. A 19th-century influence was its use as the name of the central character in  Charlotte Brontë's  novel Jane Eyre (  1847 ). From  1932 to 1959  it was used as the name of a cheerful and scantily clad beauty whose adventures were chronicled in a strip cartoon in the Daily Mirror. It is also borne by the American film stars  Jane Russell  (  1921–2011 ) and  Jane Fonda  (  b. 1937 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Johanna de Predelathe was born about 1208 as the daughter of Sir Nicholas of Predelathe. She had at least 1 son with Sir John Wishart III."},"et":{"about 1208–":"umbes 1208–Surnud","1208–Female":"1208–Surnud","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","1206":"1206","about 1208":"umbes 1208","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","1308":"1308","about 1240":"umbes 1240","1208":"1208","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1208–":"noin 1208–Kuollut","1208–Female":"1208–Kuollut","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1182–Male":"1182–Kuollut","1206":"1206","about 1208":"noin 1208","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","1308":"1308","about 1240":"noin 1240","1208":"1208","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1208–":"environ 1208–Décédée","1208–Female":"1208–Décédée","1206–Male":"1206–Décédé","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1182–Male":"1182–Décédé","1206":"1206","about 1208":"environ 1208","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","1308":"1308","about 1240":"environ 1240","1208":"1208","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Johanna de Predelathe est née environ 1208, fille de Sir Nicholas of Predelathe. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir John Wishart III."},"de":{"about 1208–":"um 1208–Verstorben","1208–Female":"1208–Verstorben","1206–Male":"1206–Verstorben","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1182–Male":"1182–Verstorben","1206":"1206","about 1208":"um 1208","1240":"1240","1182":"1182","1308":"1308","abo